I don't work out hardly ever. I think I'm fat. In my mind I deserve to be fat because I dont' work out and  i dont' watch what I eat. So therefore, whether it's true or not, I think I'm fat. Also the same thing with grades. I have decent grades, but upon looking at the list of the peopel that i know that got Straight A's last semester I start feeling dumpy about the grades I got. I think to myself "maybe if I had tried harder and studied more. It's my own fault. I'm just lazy and stupid." Even though my grades are pretty good. 
The thing is about how I look though. I could be extremely gorgeous and I would get attention. But the thing is there are about 1,000 other extremely gorgeous women at OBU. Who the heck cares? Why would I be any different than them. I'd be one of the many. So I guess the only thing I should measure myself by is my character and my unique personality. But I ask one thing. Megan Spunkelmier was an American missionary in Africa who liked to explore the land. One day Megan stumbled across a rare wild blue turkey. It became her companion. She named him Mr. Jiggles. This wasn't the kind of turkey that you eat for Thanksgiving. It was so awesome. One day she discovered that it also had the most beautiful feces she had ever seen. It was sparkly and blue with diamonds in it and it smelled like blueberries. Megan took its poop to a national science museum and tried to sell it but no one believed it was poop. So she took it to her father's chemistry lab. He said he had never seen anything so beautiful and rare but it was not poop. Megan cried for nights and cried out to God "God why do they persecute me? Why wont' they believe me? I know that this is a new scientific discovery!" God answered her the next night, "Megan no one believes you because you are wrong. It's not poop. And Mr. Jiggles is NOT a real turkey. What you have discovered a Thanksgiving play-do machine that looks like a turkey. Of course it's pretty poop, why would kids want to play with real poop? Ok scratch that. Anyway. Sorry Megan. But it's just a toy. Now go back to Africa and tell some more people about Jesus!" "Yes sir!" she said, and Megan saved many a person.

THE END
